                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-461" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>MICHAEL CONWAY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable H</hi> 138.) I produce a certificate of the prisoner's former conviction, by the name of James Spencer, which I got at Mr. Clark's office—(<hi rend="italic">read—Convicted 6th Mayt 1844, and confined six months</hi>)—he is the person, and he has been twice summarily convicted since.</p>
